### API Gateway checks
### Scope: gateway actuator + gateway auth route forwarding

@gatewayBase = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

# Keep these unique when rerunning.
@username = gateway_user_{{$timestamp}}
@email = gateway_user_{{$timestamp}}@example.com
@password = TestPassword123

### 1) Gateway health (expect 200)
GET {{gatewayBase}}/actuator/health
Accept: application/json

###
### 2) Gateway routes (expect 200)
GET {{gatewayBase}}/actuator/gateway/routes
Accept: application/json

###
### 3) Gateway route filters (expect 200)
GET {{gatewayBase}}/actuator/gateway/routefilters
Accept: application/json

###
### 4) Register via gateway -> auth-service (expect 201)
POST {{gatewayBase}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

> {%
client.global.set("gatewayAuthToken", response.body.token);
%}

###
### 5) Login via gateway -> auth-service (expect 200)
POST {{gatewayBase}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

> {%
client.global.set("gatewayAuthToken", response.body.token);
%}

###
### 6) Logout via gateway with token (expect 200)
POST {{gatewayBase}}/api/v1/auth/logout
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{gatewayAuthToken}}

{}

###
### 7) Quantity route check via gateway (expected 200 only when quantity service is up)
GET {{gatewayBase}}/api/v1/quantities
Authorization: Bearer {{gatewayAuthToken}}

